OL,5,Cthink tank
OL,7,FBut others see greater public
OL,8,Fparticipation as a way of expanding
OL,9,Fthe range of opinions considered when
OL,10,Fmaking policy.
OL,12,FOne anonymous political adviser quoted
OL,13,Fby Demos said: "Politics is very
OL,14,Fcentralised. So the views that matter
OL,15,Fare quite narrow. And much of it is
OL,16,Ffor the theatre of Westminster and
OL,17,Ffeeding the lobby, rather than what it
OL,18,Falso needs to be about, which is
OL,19,Factual delivery for citizens."
